Write Up: The first game of the year is sometimes a bit crazy, but this was a great game. Goffstown jumped out quickly but could not hold off Hooksett for long.  Back and forth, the teams scored never taking more than a 2 point lead over the other team until the 4th quarter.  Down by 3, the Goffstown Grizzlies scored three goals to tie it up.  With 1 minute left and the ball, Hooksett took 4 shots that were stopped by Goffstown goalie Matt Lamparell.  The game ended in a tie, but both teams looked terrific and will probably see eachother again this season.
